<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4747143>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 1. Onychocella angulosa (Reuss). (a–c) Recent, Madeira, NHMUK 1911.10.1.640; (a) group of autozooids and avicularia; (b) avicularium; (c) two ovicellate autozooids (arrowed), two non-ovicellate autozooids and an avicularium. (d)–(f) Middle Miocene (Badenian), St Margarethen, Burgenland, Austria, NHMUK BZ 8212 (Pitt Collection); (d) group of autozooids and avicularia; (e) avicularium; (f) early astogeny with ancestrula at centre. Scale bars: a, d, f = 500 µm; b, c, e = 200 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4747143/files/figure.png" .

